The Senator representing Ondo South Senatorial District has sacked a total of 92 aides working for him. The Senator, Nicholas Tofowomo announced the disengagement of the aides on Friday. According to the senator, the sack of 92 non-statutory political aides takes effect from July 24, 2020. The 92 aides were appointed last year shortly after he won the senatorial election in 2019. Tofowomo, in a statement signed by his media aide, Olumide Akinrinlola said a reconstitution of new aides would be communicated later at the appropriate time.